STORYLINE

Kohinoor is the story of a character named as Kohinoor (played by Sweta Khadka). Abhisekh Kharel also known as Babu (played by Shree Krishna Shrestha) saves the life of a police from a criminal Tiger. After which a minister gets inspired and he gets a job at Manpower Company. He works under Deepak. Deepak sends Nepali young girls to Israel on a working visa by means of his company. All those girls are sent to Israel from India. Abhisekh goes to India with few girls and he drops them to one of the agent in India. Then he meets an Indian man named as Rathod. Rathod takes Abhisekh to prostitution area where he meets Kohinoor. Abhisekh finds that Kohinoor has been brought in the field of prostitution from his company by using his name but Kohinoor is unaware of Abhisekh’s face. She hates man whose name is Abhisekh of that Manpower Company. Abhisekh feels guilty and takes Kohinoor away from that place with some tricks. They run away to Goa and try to go back to Nepal. And the story moves further where you can know whether Kohinoor finds out the guy who saved her is the same guy whom she was searching? Will Abhisekh be able to say her? Will they find out who is involved and how this business of selling girls to India has been running in Nepal? Will the love between Kohinoor and Abhisekh becomes success?
